# ViewModel Patterns

## Standard Structure
Every ViewModel follows the same shape:
```kotlin
@HiltViewModel
class RideDetailViewModel @Inject constructor(
    private val getRideDetailUseCase: GetRideDetailUseCase,
    savedStateHandle: SavedStateHandle
) : ViewModel() {

    private val rideId: String = checkNotNull(savedStateHandle["rideId"])

    private val _uiState = MutableStateFlow<RideDetailUiState>(RideDetailUiState.Loading)
    val uiState: StateFlow<RideDetailUiState> = _uiState.asStateFlow()

    // One-shot events (snackbars, navigation) via Channel
    private val _events = Channel<RideDetailEvent>(Channel.BUFFERED)
    val events: Flow<RideDetailEvent> = _events.receiveAsFlow()

    init { loadRide() }

    fun onAction(action: RideDetailAction) {
        when (action) {
            is RideDetailAction.Retry -> loadRide()
            is RideDetailAction.Call  -> dialPhone(action.phone)
        }
    }
}
```

## UiState — sealed class per screen
```kotlin
sealed class RideDetailUiState {
    object Loading : RideDetailUiState()
    data class Success(val ride: RideUiModel) : RideDetailUiState()
    data class Error(val message: String) : RideDetailUiState()
}
```

## UiEvent for one-shot side effects
```kotlin
sealed class RideDetailEvent {
    data class DialPhone(val number: String) : RideDetailEvent()
    data class ShowError(val message: String) : RideDetailEvent()
}
```

## Error Handling in ViewModels
```kotlin
private fun loadRide() {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        _uiState.value = RideDetailUiState.Loading
        getRideDetailUseCase(rideId)
            .onSuccess { _uiState.value = RideDetailUiState.Success(it.toUiModel()) }
            .onFailure { _uiState.value = RideDetailUiState.Error(it.localizedMessage ?: "Error") }
    }
}
```

## Collect State Safely in Compose
```kotlin
val uiState by viewModel.uiState.collectAsStateWithLifecycle()
```
Always use `collectAsStateWithLifecycle` (not `collectAsState`) to respect lifecycle.
